commit.message:
Increasing number of communication between shards

It is needed to make rotations happen in adequate time
The code now crashes with NUM_TX > 0 frequently, I fixed one of the issues in the fork choice rule, but some still exist

Generalizing the fork choice to support switches and orbits

Generalizing the fork choice rule so that it works for arbitrary number of shards
Few comments:
 - Launching with `orbit` flag will only run two shards with many orbits
 - Launching with `switch` flag will run 6 shards, do 3-4 switch and no orbits
 - Launching without flags will run 6 shards, one 3-4 switch and two orbits
I reduced the variance of the validator weights, and made blocks in 0, 1, 3 and 4 produced more often to make the demo run faster, but due to high forkfulness it still spends a lot of time in intermediate states.
fixed another memory bug, added multiple shard rotations
fixed memory errors and a faulty assert, now the swap happens successfully most of the time, and with one known source consistency error

added new fork choice and 'orbit mode' to try to show change in root shard, which sometimes works successfully! This after previous fork choice rule shown to be defficient. Some changes made also to the way the fork choice rule is called during block production. Still lots of bugs all around!
fixed bugs introced by removing the MessagesLog class in the last commit

introduced new fork choice implementation which should not suffer from infinite loops with arbitrary shard rotation, removed the MessagesLog class, replacing them with dicts in the block class, other minor changes

commit.message:
Fixing the inconsistency issues with switching

The most critical bug was in fork_choice -- it was using the parent_ID of the starting node, not the node under consideration (Vlad even mentioned at some point that it was probably the bug)
Also some hackery in the make_block to have proper neighbors at proper times

commit.message:
Copying received_log instead of pointing to the same memory solves quite a few issues with rotation

I can't find the place where either gets modified, but this definitely solves the issues with nodes not picking up each other after a switch.
With this change and Instant Broadcast switching works like a charm.
Without the instant broadcast it still gets to inconsistent sources.
